defaultThe Ministry of Justice has conceded that applications for release from detention on bail or temporary admission, and judicial reviews challenging the legality of detention would 
defaultbe
default exempt from the residence test (Ministry of Justice September 2013 
defaultTransforming Legal Aid: Next Steps, Annex B: Response to consultation, 
defaultParagraph 125). 
defaultHowever, civil claims for compensation 
defaultand damages 
defaultfor periods of unlawful detention, made after re
defaultlease, would be subject to the residence test. If the decision under challenge – in this case to maintain detention – is withdrawn by the Home Office before the decision of the court is handed down, or an injunction ordering release is sought and granted, 
defaultthen any public law elements of the unlawful detention judicial review become academic and must be determined as part of a separate civil claim for damages.
